$ Accessing and calling DLLs from VBA: returning a char array

This example tries to demonstrate how it is possible to return a character (`char`) array from a DLL and to convert it to a multibyte String (that VBA internally uses)
using the → Windows/development/WinAPI[WinAPI] function `MultiByteToWideChar`.

{ dll.c

  gh|VBA-calls-DLL|/return-char-array/dll.c||

}
{ vba.bas

  gh|VBA-calls-DLL|/return-char-array/vba.bas||

}
